From: nolarose
Subject: fix: guard null pointer in Heap.isOwned before calling mi_heap_check_owned

`isOwned` accepts `?*anyopaque` but passes it directly to
`mi_heap_check_owned`, which is declared as taking `*const anyopaque`
(non-optional). When `p` is null the raw optional bits are forwarded
to the C function, which dereferences a guaranteed-non-null pointer â€”
undefined behavior.

Return false early for null, unwrap otherwise.

---
 src/allocators/mimalloc.zig | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/allocators/mimalloc.zig b/src/allocators/mimalloc.zig
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/src/allocators/mimalloc.zig
+++ b/src/allocators/mimalloc.zig
@@ -62,7 +62,8 @@ pub const Heap = opaque {
     }

     pub fn isOwned(self: *Heap, p: ?*anyopaque) bool {
-        return mi_heap_check_owned(self, p);
+        const ptr = p orelse return false;
+        return mi_heap_check_owned(self, @ptrCast(ptr));
     }
 };
